		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Virtual LAN</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>A <b>virtual <a href="/wiki/Local_area_network" title="Local area network">LAN</a></b>, commonly known as a <b>VLAN</b>, is a group of hosts with a common set of requirements that communicate as if they were attached to the <a href="/wiki/Broadcast_domain" title="Broadcast domain">Broadcast domain</a>, regardless of their physical location. A VLAN has the same attributes as a physical <a href="/wiki/Local_area_network" title="Local area network">LAN</a>, but it allows for end stations to be grouped together even if they are not located on the same <a href="/wiki/Network_switch" title="Network switch">network switch</a>. Network reconfiguration can be done through software instead of physically relocating devices.</p>
